=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native
=head1 Description

L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native> is the interface implemented by all widgets that have
their own L<Gnome::Gdk4::Surface|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Surface>.

The obvious example of a L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native> is L<Gnome::Gtk4::Window|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Window>.

Every widget that is not itself a L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native> is contained in one,
and you can get it with L<.get-native() in class Widget|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Widget#get-native>.

To get the surface of a L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native>, use L<.get-surface()|#get-surface>.
It is also possible to find the L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native> to which a surface
belongs, with L<.Native.get-for-surface().Native.get-for-surface() in package Gnome::Gtk4|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/T-native#Native.get-for-surface>.

In addition to a L<Gnome::Gdk4::Surface|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Surface>, a L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-Native> also provides
a L<Gnome::Gsk4::Renderer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gsk4/Renderer> for rendering on that surface. To get the
renderer, use L<.get-renderer()|#get-renderer>.

